x: There are 15 trees in the grove. Grove workers will plant trees in the grove today. After they are done, there will be 21 trees. How many trees did the grove workers plant today?

Shawn has five toys. For Christmas, he got two toys each from his mom and dad. How many toys does he have now?

z: There are 15 trees originally. Then there were 21 trees after some more were planted. So there must have been 21 - 15 = 6.

Shawn started with 5 toys. If he got 2 toys each from his mom and dad, then that is 4 more toys. 5 + 4 = 9.

A bakery had 120 cookies in the morning. By the afternoon, they had baked more and had a total of 200 cookies. So, 200 - 120 = 80 cookies must have been baked in the afternoon.
Olivia had 23 dollars. 5 bagels for 3 dollars each will be 5 x 3 = 15 dollars. So she has 23 - 15 dollars left. 23 - 15 is 8.
There were originally 9 computers. For each of 4 days, 5 more computers were added. So 5 * 4 = 20 computers were added. 9 + 20 is 29.
Originally, Leah had 32 chocolates. Her sister had 42. So in total they had 32 + 42 = 74. After eating 35, they had 74 - 35 = 39.
There are originally 3 cars. 2 more cars arrive. 3 + 2 = 5.
Initially, there were 6 bicycles at the park. Later on, 4 more bicycles arrived. Consequently, there were 6+4=10 bicycles in total.

A basket contained 30 apples to begin with. After selling some at the farmers market, there were only 18 apples left in the basket. Therefore, 30−18=12 apples must have been sold.
Samantha had 3 dolls. She received 2 dolls from her grandmother and 2 dolls from her aunt, adding up to 2+2=4 more dolls. Now, Samantha has 3+4=7 dolls.
There were originally 7 fish in the aquarium. Later, the total number of fish in the aquarium increased to 13. Thus, 13 - 7 = 6 fish must have been added to the aquarium.
Jason started with 20 lollipops. Then he had 12 after giving some to Denny. So he gave Denny 20 - 12 = 8.
A parking lot had 25 cars parked in it. Later in the day, there were 47 cars in the parking lot. Hence, 47 - 25 = 22 cars must have arrived and parked in the lot during that time.
Michael started with 58 golf balls. After losing 23 on tuesday, he had 58 - 23 = 35. After losing 2 more, he had 35 - 2 = 33 golf balls.
A library started with a collection of 300 books. After receiving a new shipment, the library's collection grew to 450 books. Therefore, 450 - 300 = 150 new books must have arrived.
A farmer had 50 apple trees in his orchard. After planting more trees, he ended up with a total of 80 apple trees. Thus, 80 - 50 = 30 new apple trees were planted by the farmer.
